ent. I should also focus on crafting valid JSON for the tests, so it aligns properly with what's expected. Let's see how it all comes together from here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"circe-literal_3 is a Scala 3 compile-time JSON string-interpolator module; its POM already brings circe-core_3 and circe-jawn_3 transitively, and circe-jawn supplies the Jawn parser needed by the macro. No Docker service, extra Maven dependency, environment variable, or system property is concretely required beyond the normal Scala generated test scaffold.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment or system properties are required. Meaningful tests should be Scala 3 tests that import io.circe.literal._ and exercise the json string interpolator with static JSON plus interpolated values, then verify the resulting io.circe.Json with normal Circe APIs.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Java-only tests would not exercise the primary API because json is a Scala 3 string interpolator macro.\",\n    \"The macro implementation runs at Scala compile time, so native-image runtime coverage will mainly exercise the generated Circe Json values rather than the macro parser itself.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d66918e7a5f4065016a3f96ff6534819381d464808ced33d0\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1302, "output": 666, "cacheRead": 42496, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44464, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782552309713, "responseId": "resp_0d66918e7a5f4065016a3f96f64a748193b2d06b688b238837"}}
